## Review follow-ups addressed (from the ClawSweeper review of 4470752)

- **[P1] Real behavior proof**: added above — owned test-call run on the real server binary showing the `openai.ws.closed` disconnect event, exactly one Twilio close (2 ms after the provider TCP kill), completed cleanup (disconnect record is the final log line), and a healthy server afterward (second full call + `/health` on the same process).
- **[P3] CHANGELOG entry removed** — release notes left to the release process; the user-visible context lives in this PR body and the commit message.

## Risk notes

- `onClose` is added as a **required** member of `OpenAIRealtimeClient`, so the type system forces every consumer (and test fake) to acknowledge the disconnect path; the existing fakes gained a one-line stub.
- `OPENAI_REALTIME_URL` defaults to the existing hardcoded endpoint — no behavior change unless explicitly set. It is validated through the same `envUrl` path as the other URL vars.
- `vox simulate` constructs the same client but registers no `onClose`; its behavior is unchanged (a disconnect there already surfaces to the operator when the next send produces no response — wiring simulate teardown is a separate concern, happy to follow up).
- Security: no dependency, workflow, permission, or secret-handling changes.
